Use of the framework name and its principles in derivative works should
preserve attribution to Loi's research lineage.

The HTTP REST backend reuses architectural patterns from MHC-L
(`mcp_server/` package) authored by the same upstream project. License
compatibility: MHC-L is permissively licensed; MHC-H imports those
patterns under AGPL v3 of this repository.

The Claude plugin format follows the convention established by BeccarIA
(`legal-tech-cowork/beccaria`), which itself derives from Anthropic's
claude-for-legal snapshot. MHC-H is functionally independent and
separately licensed.
